YAML Header

I set some useful default preset.

code chunk

code chunk options

eval = FALSE : prevents code from being evaluated. you can use this when coding test. include = FALSE : runs the code, but don’t show the code or results echo = FALSE : only prevents the code chunk from appearing error = True : cause the render to continue even if codes returns an error. cache = TRUE : will save the output of the chunk on disc. note that even if the ‘.csv’ files in code change, the code chunk does not rerun. message = FALSE/warning = FALSE : do not show the messages or warnings. results = “hide” or fig.show = “hide”

knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE) : setting global options.
